<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,151,388]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,292,316]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[321,405,293,316]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paulagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[321,405,293,316]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">P. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[616,742,293,316]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paulagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[616,742,293,316]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">P. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having comparatively smaller pits on the pronotum, scutellum and basal half of forewings, two fuscous triangles at the basal angels of the scutellum, position of claval cross veins and robust and short aedeagus. It is named after its collector Dr. T.C. Maa.
</paragraph>
